*The first 3 digits after D90 specify the board model, the two digits :after that is the market (ISP) the router is being used/distributed by. :''Westell'' isn't specifying what ISP 32730 is for.
So, D90-32730 should be equivalent to the ''Verizon Westell VersaLink'' 327 :with model [[Westell VersaLink 327W (D90-327W15-06)]]. :Last 2 digits would believe to be the version.
CPU is part # TNETD7200GDW.
*The default SSID appears to be '''WESTXXXX''' where '''XXXX''' :is the last 4 digits of the router serial number.
